# SSH-server:

## Client steps:
1. create keys: conf/.ssh/keygen.sh
2. setup client user on server: `docker composer exec -it ssh-server /home/create_proxy_user.sh username < id_ed25519.pub`
3. setup socks5://ssh-proxy:1080 in conf/ext_proxies.txt

manual test:
1. `ssh -vvv -D 0.0.0.0:1081 -N -C -i ./id_ed25519 username@127.0.0.1 -p 443`
2. `curl -v -x socks5://127.0.0.1:1081 'http://ya.ru'`


# MTProto-server:
1. start the server
2. register it with telegram bot: https://t.me/mtproxybot
3. set received tag in the Telegram client


#### hints
`cat ~/my-certificate.pub >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys`

`ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -b 256` [-f ./id_ed25519]
`ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096` [-f ./id_rsa4096]
